  <a href="#1" id="1">
   A State Flood Control and Drought Relief Headquarters spokesmen said today
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   that floods along the Xijiang, Beijiang, Xiangjiang and Ganjiang have receded, except for a section of the Xijiang in Wuzhou.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   Floods hit Guangdong and several other provinces following heavy June storms.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   The provincial government yesterday urged localities
  </a>
  <a href="#5" id="5">
   to assist victims
  </a>
  <a href="#6" id="6">
   and has allocated grain, cash reserves and farm production supplies to the flood-stricken areas.
  </a>
  <a href="#7" id="7">
   Additionally, 790 million yuan in loans and donations were sent to the disaster area.
  </a>
  <a href="#8" id="8">
   CPC Central Committee Secretariat member Wen Jiabao inspected flood areas
  </a>
  <a href="#9" id="9">
   and stated production should be promptly resumed to mitigate economic losses.
  </a>
